<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: 30 SHD KNIGHT TROLL</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-17 20:26:05</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Got this one of a eurotin guard in Dalnir was lucky to get in a random rool in a group of 3 a iksar shamen me a troll sk and an enchanter, the guards are hard to kill so make sure you have a decent group. I had to harm touch the guard for 301 hp and still almost died the shamen kept me alive by healing and the enchanter casted spells to support. im gessing the guard must be lev 33 to lev 35 not quite sure on the level of the guard but he was hard to fight for a lev 30 sk troll. If you go to get this sword get a good group with a healer in it.With my 130 str i swing for an advrage of 32hp and have made hits of up to 40 hp. Ilike the speed of this sword also 36 delay and the + 5 AC is a bonus. Overall a nice sword    A TROLL SHADOW KNIGHT FROM NIGHT KEEP.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Gilraven</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-19 09:31:15</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Minor correction...not ALL coerced mobs in Dalnir are summoned. Iksar and Goblin coerced are not, but all others are. This does indeed drop off random coerced mobs as do several other weapons like the iksar staves and froglok smashers. Pretty nice weapon. at level 30 with 100 str, 92 skill (so far) I'm getting lots of dual 34 point hits. Frankly though it's the AC that should attract a ranger's attention to this blade.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Dismaul Horizons</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-24 15:32:54</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>To the guy named SHD Knight Troll above:  Get your thoughts and facts together before posting man, its distracting to others in the dungeon when people come in asking ooc "where do the guards spawn?".  There ARE NO "GUARDS" in Dalnir.  This item will drop off of "a coerced erudite" in the crypt... both times I found it, it was on the first floor in the leftmost room as you go in from Warslik Woods.  They are lore so I gave the first one to a paladin friend since I'm and enchanter and have no use for it.  I suppose I'll give the one I got last night to my new Iksar SK that I created for purposes of finding Greenmist... which is mentioned in journal entries found in Dalnir.  Restating the above post, the only thing that appears to wield it's weapon (mainly due to class restrictions of the carrier I think) is the Coerced Goblin whom wields the Goblin Flamberge.  The erudite that dropped the guard blade for my group in both instances was casting magician spells, and had an elemental pet, which would clarify the not wielding thing.</font></td></tr></table>
